social_posts.post_text: Local gremlin and her bf buy a trailer and run shirtless down the coast 🤠 for those of yall that don't know, I'm figuring my way out on the road and documenting our fun / struggles / sights / whatever we wanna share over at @birdiesbunkhouse 🌲🏕 I eventually hope to be filming and uploading YouTube, but for right now I'm focusing on documenting the fun and managing mental health during 1) the roughest season for mental health 2) this insane upheaval of any comfort zone I've built 🫠 I'm SO thankful for this opportunity, and I'm excited to learn what this teaches me

You should be better at hiking. You should be more interesting. But you shouldn't be so fake on social media. You shouldn't be corny though. You need to make better content. You need to make more content. You should want babies. You should have a career. You should be married by now. 
.
This line hits me like a ton of bricks every time I listen to it. I just want to be too soft for all of it. I'm trying to allow myself the softness and the fluidity I've never allowed myself to have
.
The softness to be at peace with where I am in life instead of my own pounding, harsh self-criticism.
.
The fluidity to continue moving through at my own pace. And flowing through unexpected shifts and junctions. 
.
I would have never expected where I am now, HIKING? In a trailer? Away from my comfort people? Away from my safe spaces? Keep flowing. Keeeep it flowing. Embrace the softness. 🌸

Ngl yall I've been having a full on identity crisis. This life shift with @birdiesbunkhouse has thrown me for 👏 a 👏 loop 👏 and call me silly but I was noooot expecting it. I really appreciate yall who are still on here interacting with me, and who started following our other page. I'm not feeling super like myself and I'm taking time to develop the next version of her. Here's to all the  almost-thirty-what-the-hell-am-I-doing-with-my-life vibes 🤷‍♀️💖 may they inspire us to take new and unexpected directions, and give us moments to practice kindness when we speak to ourselves.

29 and Feeling Fine 🥳💫 The last couple years I've said I feel like every year closer to 30 I gain an infinity stone. One more year of gaining strength and the guts to fully transform into my Thanos-level feminine power 😈💫

I thought I had a bad year, and then looking back at the pictures and videos I realized that would be completely unfair to myself and my loved ones to say that. While this year kicked my ass in so many ways- this year was also kick-ass in SO MANY more ways ❤️ 
.
I saw Avril Lavigne and by pure luck got floor seats I didn't pay for.
.
 I saw ADTR & The Used which turned into the most heartwarming hometown friends' reunion.
.
I saw The Story So Far and My Chem with one of my dearest friends and shared the most emotional concert experience of my life.
.
The most random, unexpected place in BC became a true home to me, and I had some of the best memories of my summer there with some of the kindest people I've ever met.
.
I worked hard and manifested a dream of mine to travel into reality
.
I gained a partner who sees me for who I am and encourages and inspires me every day. 
.
❤️ these were truly just some of the best parts. And in 2023 I know I need to focus on these parts. These are the things that matter, that got me through, the days I went to bed with a huge smile on my face. Spending time with the people who make me feel loved for exactly who I am. ❤️

I hope you get a chance to take stock of these kinds of memories before we hop into the new year, life is really beautiful if you open your heart to the beauty in your life 🌻

Some days you just have to make yourself some tea, a vegan Lunchable,  and sit and cry while watching comfort YouTubers. Today was one of those days. Today was a day even just staying in a neutral frame of mind was a struggle. At one point it felt like a part of my brain had separated, and almost parented the over-tired, over-emotional other side of my brain. Saying, "it's okay you're feeling like this. you might just need some food and something relaxing, and maybe something that makes you happy. Let's get that going- okay?"
.
One of the best things I've learned in therapy has taught me is to step back and ask why I'm feeling the way I am. To sit in the feeling, accept the feeling, and come to it with kindness. Which can be SO hard. Especially if you're like me and sometimes feel like you constantly need to be happy, productive, etc in order feel worthy.
.
I hope you're able to meet those moments with kindness. Let's work on doing that more together, okay? okay. 💕

Since the shift out of the 2012-2016 makeup era of baking, dipbrow, and fullest coverage foundations ever- what has been the biggest changes in your makeup routine? What have you been de-influenced from lately? I'm genuinely soo curious!
.
I now wear pressed powder because I simply cannot be bothered to have two different powders for my face versus under eyes
.
I now wear bronzer as eyeshadow which I LITERALLY would have like never done before. You NEED eyeshadow- duh 🙄 this goes for SO many things that could double as another, but influencers/companies tell you that you need both. 
.
I think the BIGGEST thing for me was just wearing the makeup I want to wear (or not) and not worrying about current makeup trends. I hate wearing mascara- I feel like it weirdly makes my eyes look smaller. But I'm still gonna wear base and bronzer and brows 🤷‍♀️

March 2023 versus March 2020 🖤 Long winded post about why I abandoned tiktok and never looked back ahead. 

I've been seeing this comparison about where we were all at during the start of the pandemic versus where we are now and it got me in. My. FEELINGS. Do I miss 2020 Era Katie? Tiktok "fame" Katie? In a lot of ways, yes. Because as someone who has spent 10 years creating content for the internet, 2020 was FINALLY the year where I felt like I "made it". I had an impressive enough number of followers, made fun, relatable, and sometimes hilariously cringy content, and I had so much fun doing it.

But it was the fucking loneliest time of my LIFE. And Tiktok drove me absolutely crazy. I would spend HOURS on a 10 second clip I was so proud of only for it to flop. I would obsess night after night after spending hours scrolling stressing like, I NEED to be the next on this trend, with this sound, I need to be more clever, more funny, hotter etc etc etc ETC. and it turned into a vicious cycle and was really tough on me mentally. I am not exaggerating when I say that content mining took over my life at the time.

And I'm not breaking any mold by saying I turned to tiktok for community and for boredom sake during the pandemic. As most of you know, I was separated from my partner at the time and was lonely and bored, so it served a purpose as it did/does for us most of the time

But getting my account deleted was the biggest blessing in disguise. Once I took a SOLID break from tiktok and calmed down and realized all the harm it was doing to me mentally, I realized I was better off without it.

Which kinda feels like a nail in the coffin for any influencer? If you can't keep up with the newest trend, the newest way to use a platform? To quote Wendy Williams, DEATH. DEATH TO ALL OF YOU. 

But HONESTLY that's what it felt like. But once the dust had settled, I realized tiktok tossed me into a complete tailspin of constant comparison. Once I finally broke out of it, I started only posting when I WANTED to. And the people who still follow me are the true friends I need. (Contined in comments)

Don't waste your life's purpose worrying about your body 🖤 I loved this audio so much. Especially as someone who in their early 20s as I lost my teenage body and shifted into a more womanly body. I gained weight around my thighs, and I never wanted to wear shorts, I hated how short my legs were, I hated that they werent smooth. I hated so many things about my legs. 
.
And it is truly such a waste. A waste of energy. A waste of potential experiences. A waste of precious brain power that could be used to propel you forward.
.
It's not our fault- society, sometimes our friends or family, media, they all tell us that's exactly what we should use our brain power for.
.
But once you can break yourself free and simply just see your body for what it is- your vessel, your home. It frees up that energy to finally be used for good ✨️ 
.
Your body is YOUR BODY. That's all it needs to do. That's all it needs to be. Treat it kindly

Stories saw the new PFP first 😎 
It's a new Kittysnack Era, so it's time to shift the profile photo accordingly. Here's some things I've been embracing lately that mark differences in how I see and present myself.
🩷 COLOR!!! WEARING COLOR! I'm not feeling the need to stick myself into my "I have to wear all black to show I'm edgy" box. Wearing bright color and feeling so much ease and joy doing so. 
🩷 Natural, glowing makeup, but still allowing myself to have fun with NO pressure of it looking Instagram perfect.
🩷 A more body neutral approach to my self-love (but it's taken years of strong body positive messaging to myself in order to get here) 
🩷 100% curated photos to maybe 20% curated photos. While yes- I'm still posing both my face and body, I am no longer feeling the need to have a full-blown photoshoot just to create a picture that I feel is "Instagram worthy."
.
I've just felt more at ease overall with how I present myself to the world, and it's been a breath of fresh air and freedom I've never felt in my life.
